Fore legs modified (
Figs 51, 52
); profemora with longer, subtruncate process, bearing fringe of stiff setae subapically; protibiae with pointed protrusion on median and angular lobule on lateral side; penultimate tarsomere widened/flattened distally, with terminal tarsomere articulated dorsally near base in all tarsi. Setation normally developed; pro- and mesotibiae with two, metatibiae with single terminal spur.

Abdominal sternum VII moderately emarginate, with small, median setose protuberance dorsally (
Fig. 53
). Tergum VII simple, subtruncate posteriorly. Sternite VIII (
Fig. 54
); paired prongs with narrow, setose lobe laterally. Tergite VIII with simple paired sclerites nearly evenly rounded apically, narrowly connected medially. Terminal sclerite of segment IX (spiculum) membranous, evenly rounded apically. Aedeagus (
Fig. 55
); apical portion of tegmen 0.5 times as long as basal-piece, with small lateral lobules apically.
